cuisine: French
servings: 2
---

Remove the @duck breasts{2} from the fridge at least ~{30%minutes} before cooking if you can. Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cut slices across the duck skin with a sharp #knife{}. Rub the zest from half the @orange{1} onto the breasts along with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

> The more you cut into the skin, the easier it is for the fat to be released.

Cut the @new potatoes{1} into quarters and cook in your boiling water for ~{10%minutes} or until cooked, then drain and put to the side with a lid on.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Segment the orange by cutting off the top and bottom. Cut off the remaining skin and pith (following the shape of the orange). Finally, over a #bowl{} cut out the segments of fruit by cutting in between the membranes. Squeeze what's left of the orange to collect as much juice as possible.

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @spring onion{1}(chopped into thin discs) and separate the white parts from the green. Cut the @chicory{2} in half lengthways. Bash the cooked potatoes with a #potato masher{} or a #fork{}, add the whites of the spring onions along with @salt{1/4%tsp}, a grind of @pepper{1%grind} and @butter{1%tbsp} or @olive oil{}. Put the lid on again and set aside.

Lay the duck breasts in a cold frying pan skin-side down. Cook on medium-low heat for about ~{8%minutes} or until the fat is crisp and golden. Transfer to a #baking dish{} skin-side up and cook for ~{5%minutes} on the top shelf of your oven.

Use the same pan in which you fried the duck and remove all but @?excess fat{1%tbsp}. Lay your chicory in, flat-side down and cook on high for ~{5%minutes} until golden. Add @?sugar{1%tsp} and cook for ~{1%minute} to caramelise. Add @water{250%ml} to your pan with @chicken stock pot{1/2}, bring to a simmer, cover with a #lid{} and cook for ~{5-8%minutes} until soft.

Remove the chicory and add the orange juice into the pan along with the @star anise{1} and allow this to reduce down over a medium heat for ~{1-2%minutes}. Mix the @cornflour{1%tsp} with @water{1%tsp} and add to the sauce along with the orange segments. Cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Serve the duck with the chicory and its sauce alongside the bashed new potatoes. Sprinkle over the reserved spring onion greens and enjoy!